<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6459250>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Scanning electron photomicrographs showing the general habitus of Iberiarmadillidium psammophilum (A), Iberiarmadillidium pinicola (B), Iberiarmadillidium sakura (C), Cristarmadillidium myrmecophilum (D) and Cristarmadillidium muricatum (E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6459250/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6459252>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Scanning electron photomicrographs showing details of pereonite 1 and 2 epimera of Iberiarmadillidium psammophilum (A), Iberiarmadillidium pinicola (B), Iberiarmadillidium sakura (C), Cristarmadillidium myrmecophilum (D) and Cristarmadillidium muricatum (E) (only epimera 1 is shown)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6459252/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6459254>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Scanning electron photomicrographs showing details of the telson of Iberiarmadillidium psammophilum (A), Iberiarmadillidium pinicola (B), Iberiarmadillidium sakura (C), Cristarmadillidium myrmecophilum (D) and Cristarmadillidium breuili (E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6459254/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

